Once you land a snare on your opponent the fight is all but over.  After opponents get decent resists though, snare will hardly ever land and makes things much more complicated.  A monkey could be trained to kill a snared opponent.  With the advent of manaburn, level 60 wizards found that burn, instagate, then reapply 2 hours later was a very effective tactic to gain points and involved little to no risk at all.  While the points board does not indicate who is necessarily the *best* pkers on the server it does indicate who pk's alot and is somewhat effective at it. <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Chris+Cojocar/fullsize/horse.jpg" border="0">
